Reasoning: The paper discusses the development of a methodology for knowledge discovery from Big Data, which involves machine learning, statistics, and database building and querying. This aligns with several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.DB (databases), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.LG (machine learning), cs.IR (information retrieval), and cs.DS (data structures and algorithms). However, given the focus on Big Data processing and clustering, cs.DB and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.LG, cs.IR, and cs.DS.
